<p>The <code>exists</code> function tests if a file exists.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}if {open}echo 'index.php' | exists{close} eq 1{close}File found{open}/if{close}</pre>
{if {echo 'index.php' | exists} eq 1}<p>Result: <b>index.php exists</b></p>{else}<p>Result: <b>index.php not found</b></p>{/if}

<h2>Check Path</h2>
<pre>{open}if {open}echo '_lib/helpers.php' | exists{close} eq 1{close}Helper exists{open}/if{close}</pre>
{if {echo '_lib/helpers.php' | exists} eq 1}<p>Found: <b>Helper file exists</b></p>{else}<p>Not found: <b>Helper file missing</b></p>{/if}

<h2>Conditional Include</h2>
<pre>{open}if {open}echo 'custom.pad' | exists{close} eq 1{close}
  {open}custom{close}
{open}/if{close}</pre>

<h2>Chained Example</h2>
<pre>{open}data $file = 'readme.txt'{close}
{open}if {open}echo $file | exists{close} eq 1{close}Found{open}/if{close}</pre>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Returns 1 (true) if file exists, 0 (false) otherwise. Path is relative to current page.</p>
